- 'High satisfaction level' means the average satisfaction level is greater than 0.5;
- 'Promoted to Level 2' indicates a specific type of promotion.

- "industrious and dedicated" refers to employees who have a high average monthly work hours;
- "high satisfaction level" is defined as an average satisfaction level greater than 0.5;
- "consistently performs well in evaluations" means an average evaluation score greater than 0.6;
